|x-y| < \delta_\epsilon
x \geq 1, y \geq 1)
|\frac{1}{x^2}-\frac{1}{y^2}| < \epsilon
\left|\frac{(y-x)(y+x)}{x^2y^2}\right| < \epsilon \tag{1}
|x-y| < \frac{\epsilon x^2 y^2}{x+y}
\delta_\epsilon < \frac{\epsilon x^2 y^2}{x+y}
\delta_\epsilon \geq \frac{\epsilon}{2}
\frac{x+y}{x^2y^2} \leq 2
\delta_\epsilon \leq \frac{\epsilon}{2}
x,y \ge 1
\left| \frac{1}{x^2} - \frac{1}{y^2} \right| = |x-y| \left| \frac{y+x}{x^2 y^2} \right| = |x-y| \left( \frac{1}{x^2 y} + \frac{1}{x y^2} \right) \le 2 |x-y|.
|x-y| < \frac{\epsilon}{2}
\left| \frac{1}{x^2} - \frac{1}{y^2} \right| < \epsilon
